  {"t":"lead","html":"Barcelona has two menus. There's the one taped to a window on La Rambla, in six languages, next to a photo of paella and a tout holding laminated pages — and there's the one three streets back, chalked on a board, in Catalan only, where the vermut is on tap and nobody's translated anything for you. This guide is about finding the second one."},
